{{1937 Big 6 football standings}}
The '''1937 Kansas State Wildcats football team''' represented [[Kansas State University]] in the [[college football]] [[1937 college football season|season of 1937]]. The [[Kansas State Wildcats football|team's]] head football coach was [[Wes Fry]], in his third year at the helm of the Wildcats. The Wildcats played their home games in [[Memorial Stadium (Kansas State)|Memorial Stadium]]. The Wildcats finished the season with a 4-5 record with a 1-4 record in conference play. They finished in a tie for last place in the [[Big 8 Conference|Big 6]].  The Wildcats scored 76 points and gave up 84 points.

